<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>what an idea • what’s the idea</xh5><p> <i>what an idea—</i>1. that’s a great idea: They don’t fit very well under the Christmas tree, but <u>what an idea</u> for that perfect gift! 2. that’s preposterous; that’s most unreasonable: Pa looked at ma stunned. Good heavens <u>what an idea</u>!</p><p> <i>what’s the idea</i>—(also: what’s the big idea) what’s the intention or purpose <i>(is usually used to question smth. that is not welcome): </i><u>What’s the idea</u> behind creating a game that’s part way between Australian Rules football and Gaelic football.</p> </entry>
